-- Brazil's economic activity rises 0.27 pct in August-central bank
-- 
-- Thu Oct 16, 2014 07:38AM EDT
-- None



BRASILIA, Oct 16 (Reuters) - The Brazilian central bank's IBC-Br economic activity index <BRIBC=ECI> rose 0.27 percent in August from July in seasonally adjusted terms, the bank said on Thursday.

The median estimate in a Reuters survey of 26 analysts was for a 0.3 percent increase.